5:
Thank you so much for coming out
to see me today, everyone!
12:
Wh-whoa! Is doing security for live
events always this hard?!
16: How the hell am I supposed to know?
20:
You know, there are some smug
adventurers out there who they
think they're hot stuff... But I'm gonna
show them who's the REAL deal!
24:
You know who I'm talking about,
don't you? Palpebra's own Levy, of
course!
29:
Uh... The crowd was already rowdy
before, but they're definitely not
gonna like that!
32:
The hell is a noob adventurer like
you doing slandering our queen
Lady Levy?!
44:
Phew... You know, the way they
described it to me, I thought the job
would be way easier...
48:
No kidding. I'm sticking to fighting
monsters from now on.
51: Gaaah! I can't believe I did it AGAIN!
55:
I went and dissed Levy in front of
everyone! How am I gonna look her
in the eyes at her next handshake
event?!
64:
No way! You get a copy of her latest
book release—SIGNED, mind
you—and a handshake! Deals like
that don't come around every day,
you know!
67:
No self-respecting fan would turn
that down!
70: Damn it, I screwed everything up...
74:
Why'd I have to go and say all those
things?!
78:
That is quite the bad habit of yours...
You get all heated up during
performances and... say provocative
things.
83:
I know I have a problem—but it's not
that easy to quit, you know! Gahh,
just KILL me already!
88:
All right, settle down. I'll go and
make you a cup of tea. That should
calm your nerves.
93:
So... You were a fan of Levy's all
along, huh?
104:
AAAAAH! You mean you heard
everything I said?!
111:
I see... So she didn't mean any of the
things she said during her
performance?
115:
Yep. That was Edita's whole appeal
from the beginning, after all. She's
bright and cheerful, but she "tells it
like it is," or whatnot.
120:
The problem is... Once you make
crazy remarks like that, people start
expecting it, so you have to keep
pushing boundaries to stay relevant!
124:
Before I knew it, this is the type of
person I became... But that wasn't
my intention!
129:
She's trying her best to improve,
bless her heart, but... She just gets
carried away on stage.
134:
If you keep that up, it could really
blow up in your face, you know.
139:
No! Anything but that! I don't want to
be canceled!
144:
Don't worry. If that does happen,
you'll just have to lay low for a while.
Palpebra will still be here when you
get back!
147:
Oh, speaking of places to hide...
Would all of you be willing to help
Edita out with her little problem?
152:
Are you using us to help people
"disappear" now?
157:
Haha, I'd be lying if I said that
thought didn't occur to me. But no,
my main goal here is to facilitate
cultural exchange.
161:
Starview Village is packed with all
sorts of people! It could be a perfect
learning opportunity for Edita here.
166:
I have to agree. Learning from the
behavior of others might be just
what she needs right about now.
187:
I mean, look at me! I can't go on like
this, lying to my fans... Something
needs to change!
191:
And if going with you can help me to
do that, then I'm willing to give it a
try!
195: What's your take on this, Nimbus?
200:
Same thing I thought before—she's
a loose cannon. Reckless too, like
Stella. If she runs her mouth...
205:
No need to worry about that! I'll be
having her sign this little bad boy
just in case!
215:
This is called an NDA—basically, it's
to ensure you won't tell anyone
about where Alk takes you.
219:
Huh? I don't really get it, but okay.
Where do I sign?
224:
Way to sign a contract without even
reading it. This girl...
233:
Despite everything we just talked
about, Edita really IS a capable
adventurer! I'm sure she'll be quite
helpful to you as well!
238:
We're looking forward to working
with her.
243: All right, Edita. Let's get going.
249:
Okay! Thanks for taking me along,
everyone!
